Gathering the forces of the giant strike
The League Trade Unions and the National Federation of Labour Commissions will constitute a strike commission on Friday to coordinate the Monday strike that will last indefinitely.
On Saturday a protest rally will be held, while on Monday - the day on which the final vote on the public health law - the labor stop will begin.
This action will certainly cause great difficulties in transport, as rail traffic will be stopped completely and workers of the Budapest Collective Transport Company will be on strike up to 13 hours.
In the afternoon of Friday, the League Trade Unions will report on the details of their Monday strike, which will be held jointly with the National Federation of Labour Commissions.
The strike commission of the LIGA and the National Machine Union will also be set up to coordinate the actions of Monday.
On Saturday, a protest rally will be held, while on Monday the participating unions will take an indefinite strike, if no agreement is reached with the government.
This means that - on the day of the parliamentary vote on the public health law - they did not report on the date of the end of the strike initiated.
If the National Assembly disapproves of the public health law, the trade unions will immediately withdraw their appeal to the strike.
Instead, if the law is passed, the strike committees will meet and decide on the future.
On the basis of the agenda of Monday of the National Assembly, it is also possible that only public health law may be voted on at very late nights, or at best near midnight.
As a result of the strike that will start on Monday, there will be significant difficulties in transport: on the railways it will cease to work indefinitely, in the morning there may be some part of the collective transport of Budapest and more than half of the inter-urban bus transport of Volán companies.
At the same time, at many points in the country, half of the roads will be closed.
Numerous trade unions and civil organizations have joined the strike, their names are constantly updated on the League's website.
Some trade unions announced their strike indefinitely, others for defined time.
Until Thursday afternoon, the State Railway and the Free Trade Union of Railway Workers (SLTF) were unable to reach agreement even on the minimum services, but as Christmas parties approached, more and more people were traveling on the trains.
According to information received so far, from the beginning of the day until 1 p.m. workers of the Budapest Collective Transport Company will be on strike, Budapest Airports from 7 to 9 a.m. will hold a four-hour strike of the Liga Trade Unions of the Electrical Industry and Thermal Energy, the Educational Unions called a strike of 2 to 8 hours and the Democratic Union of the Educators.
The Hungarian Association of Physicians will take a national strike at alternative times and the Democratic Union of Workers of the Health and Social Sector (SDTSSS) forming part of the Forum for Trade Union Cooperation will hold a two-hour warning strike.
The most important of the four claims made by the League is that the government withdraws its proposal on public health reform and submits a new conception to a social debate.
The second demand is that they gradually introduce the new form of calculation of pensions that will enter into force next year.
The third is to ensure, even before 2010, for early retirements the possibility that the occupations that deserve to enter the system.
The fourth reason for the strike is that the Free Trade Union of Railway Workers (SLTF) which is part of the League Trade Unions, does not accept the proposal of the Ministry of Economy and Transport on the railway side lines and expect another different proposal.
Political Capital[b1]: In the country the risk by the Hungarian Guard increases
According to the Risk Analysis Division (Risk Analysis Division) of the Capital Policy, the activity of the Hungarian Guard, constituted in August of this year with the support of the Movement by a Better Hungary, has increased the political risk of Hungary and the region from a number of points of view.
The company's "risk warning" is written: in relation to the activity of the Hungarian Guard, the highest political risk is that "with the worsening of the ethnic tensions existing between the Roma and non-Gypsy people of Hungary, even in the short term violent ethnic clashes may occur."
The main reason for this is that the political strategy of the Hungarian Guard is probably the provocation of such an event - the representative of the Research Institute added.
They stated that this was due to one of the main shortcomings of the protagonists of Hungarian political life: "the protagonists of public life gave public debate of the Gypsy problem to representatives of radical and extremist political groups, who were able to base their political strategy on the discrepancies between Roma and Hungarians."
This aggravates the problem, makes normal dialogue impossible, strengthens extremists and increases the likelihood of the outbreak of violent conflicts - they believe.
Moreover, according to the Research Institute, the activities of the National Guard, as a result of the high attention of the national and international average, "has significantly deteriorated Hungary's image abroad, especially with regard to the stability and democratic development of the country".
