It also expands the number of systems for the execution of financial instruments operations, so that regulated secondary markets are added to multilateral trading systems and orders internalisation systems, which will compete with the current stock exchange managers.
The Act also obliges investment service companies to disclose on the market information on key aspects of their business profile, risk exposure and risk management forms and requires them to keep a record of all operations they carry out, to facilitate supervision by CNMV.
In its passage through the Commission on the Economy of Congress, several amendments were incorporated, among which it highlights that debt securities are considered as a financial instrument "complex" given its high risk to the investor, which has been demonstrated with the debt of US high-risk mortgages (subprime).
